article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 75, Cal Poly-SLO 60
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Alex Harris scored 31 points as UC Santa Barbara beat Cal Poly 75-60 on Saturday night. Harris went 10-for-12 from the free throw line and 5-for-9 from behind the 3-point arc and James Powell added 20 points for the Gauchos (14-4, 3-2 Big West). Trae Clark and Lorenzo Keeler scored 12 apiece for Cal Poly (6-11, 1-4). The Mustangs have lost three straight. Powell made a 3-pointer to cap a 7-0 run that put UC Santa Barbara ahead for good 16-13 with 11:31 to play in the first half. The Gauchos led by as many as 21 in the second half.
